{Welcome to my  Secret Blitz Weapons: 1.e4  course. I'm excited to share with you the secrets and strategies of the 1.e4 opening that can take your blitz and rapid game to the next level. This course is designed to provide you with a repertoire of powerful and surprising weapons that will be very easy to play for White, with a clear plan.   1.e4 is one of the oldest and most popular starting moves for White; it immediately starts the fight for control of the center. This move has been favored by legends like Bobby Fischer, who declared it 'best by test'; Garry Kasparov, who used it to play some of the most spectacular games in history; and Magnus Carlsen, who continues to inspire players with his creativity and deep understanding.  Throughout this course, we are going to see a lot of fresh and unknown ideas, which I believe will lead to great results! Together, we'll discover how to play 1.e4 and take your chess to the next level!   I am a 23-year-old International Grandmaster from Armenia. I started playing chess when I was 6 years old. At the age of 12, I became World Champion in my age category, and I realized that I am stuck with chess. :) I became a GM when I was 17 years old, and at the age of 18, I began studying at Webster University in St. Louis, Missouri.  In chess camps, as a child, I loved playing blitz with my friends and later I began playing online on various websites, and now I am playing on chess.com. As I write this introduction, I am currently waiting for someone to accept my challenge of 3+0, but unfortunately, my rating is way too high, haha. :)  On chess.com, I usually rank around the top 20. Many times, I've been asked what's the secret of being good at blitz; well obviously sharpness is part of it, but openings are equally important, so I thought of creating this course for 1.e4 players.   Aram Hakobyan, June 2024} 1. Z0 *

