1. e4 e5 ({Over the last few decades, it has been very well known that} 1... e5 {is the best and most solid response to 1.e4 . Nowadays, it's impossible to find any advantage against e5 , and that's because it simply doesn't exist.  It is well known that the Berlin endgames and Ruy Lopez positions are equal, but in this course, I am excited to announce that I will cover something extremely new and interesting, which will shock and surprise our opponents, who will find it difficult to deal with against someone who is well prepared.}) 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 {With this move, we are going to the Four Knights opening, which is usually known for its drawish tendency, but our next step is going to change the opening dynamic completely.} 4. Nd5 {The move is a truly unusual one, and I am sure many of you are seeing it for the first time. First of all, it is important to note that this move isn't making a huge difference when it comes to the evaluation, so the position remains equal, but Black needs to make careful moves.  This is a very interesting idea and very fresh. I played it in two Armageddon games, which shows that I do trust this opening even in high-level games.} Nxe4 5. Qe2 {Try this move if you are playing a blitz game.} Nf6 {In my opinion, this is the most natural way to play.} 6. Nxe5 Nd4 {This is the best move, and it manages to equalize the position, but there is a chance to go wrong or to get tempted to achieve more than just simply equalizing.} (6... Nxe5 7. Qxe5+ Be7 8. Nxc7+ {, and if Nxd5 Nxc6++- .}) 7. Qc4 Nxc2+ {A very logical move. It appears that Black has won a pawn, but it is actually a blunder!} 8. Kd1 {Sacrificing the rook for the attack!} c6 ({This move is extremely challenging. Tactics such as Nb6 or Nc7 do not work, and for the moment Black is still managing to stay a pawn up for a few moves. Following} 8... Nxa1 9. Nxc7+ Ke7 10. b3 {, it is impossible to stop Ba3 + and Qxf7 +, so Black is getting mated.}) 9. Nxf6+ Qxf6 10. Ng4 {Forcing Black to go ... Qg6 .} Qg6 11. Qe2+ Be7 12. Ne5 Qf5 13. g4 {Black is finally running out of options and tricks, and right now there is no way to save the knight on c2 .} *

