ould not allow ... e4 .} dxe5 12. Qe2 {... Bd6 would allow Ng5 , and ... Bf6 is bad since the f5 -pawn would be hanging, so the most logical move is ... e4 .} Bd6 13. Ng5 Qe8 14. Ne6 Rf7 15. c4 {White protects the d5 -pawn and prepares for a possible c4 - c5 push.} e4 (15... Nf8 16. c5 {White wins a piece.}) 16. Be3 {The idea here for White is to push c4 - c5 , place the bishop on b3 , and protect the knight on e6 .} *

