ould not allow ... e4 .} dxe5 12. Qe2 {... Bd6 would allow Ng5 , and ... Bf6 is bad since the f5 -pawn would be hanging, so the most logical move is ... e4 .} Bd6 13. Ng5 Nf6 14. Ne6 Bxe6 15. dxe6 e4 16. f3 {Getting rid of Black's strong center is important, and the e6 -pawn is extremely strong, but most importantly, Black won't be able to take it soon, as Bb3 is always an option.} *

