1. e4 e5 ({Over the last few decades, it has been very well known that} 1... e5 {is the best and most solid response to 1.e4 . Nowadays, it's impossible to find any advantage against e5 , and that's because it simply doesn't exist.  It is well known that the Berlin endgames and Ruy Lopez positions are equal, but in this course, I am excited to announce that I will cover something extremely new and interesting, which will shock and surprise our opponents, who will find it difficult to deal with against someone who is well prepared.}) 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 {With this move, we are going to the Four Knights opening, which is usually known for its drawish tendency, but our next step is going to change the opening dynamic completely.} 4. Nd5 {The move is a truly unusual one, and I am sure many of you are seeing it for the first time. First of all, it is important to note that this move isn't making a huge difference when it comes to the evaluation, so the position remains equal, but Black needs to make careful moves.  This is a very interesting idea and very fresh. I played it in two Armageddon games, which shows that I do trust this opening even in high-level games.} Bc5 {A very natural developing move.} 5. c3 {This already looks dangerous for Black, as d2 - d4 is a threat right now.} O-O 6. d3 {Protecting the e4 -pawn and creating the threat of Bg5 ; b4 is also an idea to keep in mind.} (6. d4 $6 {Tactically, d4 does not work here, but I believe it would be extremely hard for our opponents to find out why it does not work so well in faster time controls.} exd4 7. cxd4 Nxd4 $1 8. Nxd4 Nxd5 9. exd5 Qh4 10. Be3 {and after many direct and only moves, here as well we have only one move to make, which is Be3 , but unfortunately, after} Re8 {, White is unable to stop both ... Rxe3 and ... Qxd4 or ... Bxd4 at the same time.}) 6... Nxd5 {I believe this is another logical approach. The knight on d5 is annoying for Black, so eliminating it while keeping equal material is quite logical.} 7. exd5 Ne7 8. Nxe5 Nxd5 9. d4 {It is important to understand that the dynamic of the game has changed, and right now we should focus on controlling the center and playing more positionally.} Be7 10. Qf3 Nf6 11. Bd3 d6 12. Nc4 {We do control the center for the moment, we have more space, and later on, castling and trying to take control of the e-file should be our main focus.} *

