n White can still put pressure on the kingside with Ng5 or Bg5 .}) 8. Re1 O-O {This move does not seem natural, but it could happen.} 9. Nxe7+ Nxe7 10. Bxh7+ {A standard Greek Gift sacrifice is winning the game.} Kxh7 11. Ng5+ Kg6 12. Qg4 f5 13. Qg3 {Now Ne6 + is a threat and Black is forced to move the king to f6 .} Kf6 14. Qe5+ Kg6 15. Qxc5 {Black's position is simply hopeless.} *

