queen to either g4 or h5 , and start the attack.} Rb8 {This move is natural, but not great. It allows us to push g5 with tempo and take more space.} 12. g5 Nd7 {It is very important to keep in mind that after ... Nd7 , White should prepare against ... e5 .} 13. Qg4 {Protecting the g5 -pawn, developing the queen to the active square, and preparing Nf3 and f5 or Nf3 and h4 - h5 with the idea of g6 .} Nd4 {Preparing ... b5 , and making an active move.} 14. Nf3 {Offering a knight trade and stopping Black's only counterplay, which is to push ... b7 - b5 .} a6 15. a4 {Stopping ... b5 completely. The ideas here are Bd2 , Rae1 , finishing development, and preparing f5 . Another idea is to push h4 - h5 with the idea of pushing g6 or h6 , depending on how things are going.} *

