1. e4 c5 ({To White's 1.e4 , the Sicilian Defense is the most popular response. The opening has a reputation for leading to very sharp positions, yet it also depends on how both sides decide to keep the game going. After} 1... c5 {, we are going to play mostly sidelines where Black has to play very carefully.}) 2. Nf3 ({This is the most logical and sound move here, simply developing the knight. Usually, the idea is to push} 2. d4 {, but in some cases, we are going to make different moves, avoiding main line theory.}) 2... d6 ({In the Sicilian,} 2... d6 {represents an attempt to play the Najdorf, among other lines.}) 3. Bb5+ {I like this move for blitz games. This avoids the well-known Najdorf, and with my suggestions, we are going to get not-so-known positions where it is easier to be White.} Nd7 {This is the main move in this position; it is very ambitious and leads to heavily theoretical lines.} (3... Nc6 {instead would transpose to the Rossolimo Variation.}) 4. O-O a6 5. Bxd7+ ({The main move here is} 5. Bd3 {, but we are looking for a different type of game, where we give away the bishop pair for activity.}) 5... Bxd7 6. c3 {The idea, once again, is very obvious. White wants to take the center with d2 - d4 .} Nf6 ({Other moves, such as} 6... e6 {or g6 , won't stop our} 7. d4 {expansion plans.}) 7. Re1 e6 8. d4 Be7 {Black is aiming to finish development as soon as possible, and the idea of not taking ... cxd4 is to keep the white knight on the bad b1 -square and not allow it to develop to c3 very easily.} 9. dxc5 dxc5 10. e5 Nd5 11. c4 {This way White is able to activate the knight, control the space in the center, and push Black's active knight away from the center.} Nb4 {Not an easy move to make, but the idea is quite smart. Black is trying to put the knight on c6 from where it keeps an eye on the e5 -pawn and d4 -square, while on b6 it does nothing.} 12. a3 Nc6 13. Nc3 {It does not matter if we play Nbd2 or Nc3 , the idea is the same. We bring the knight to e4 , and the bishop to f4 .} O-O 14. Ne4 {The knight is standing amazingly on e4 , and after Bf4 , there are a lot of ideas, such as Nd6 and Neg5 .} Qc7 15. Bf4 Rad8 16. Qc2 {White has full control over the center, and the idea right now is to go Neg5 to force ... g6 , which weakens all the dark squares, and then bring the knight back to e4 .} *

