ight with} 11... Bb4 {fails immediately to either} 12. Qg4 {or Nxe4 since Bxe1 is met by the intermediate} Nd6 {.}) 12. Nxd2 Be7 13. Re3 {It is very important to understand that White should play very actively, and Re3 is the best way to do it right now, launching an attack immediately.} O-O 14. Rg3 {White is better. The next move is Qg4 , forcing Black to play ... g6 , and after Nf3 , White will control all the dark squares.} Rc8 15. Qg4 g6 16. Nf3 {White is positionally winning; Bg5 is an idea to trade the dark-squared bishops and make the dark squares even weaker, or Qf4 with the idea of Qh6 and Rh3 .} *

