ght with} 11... Bb4 {fails immediately to either} 12. Qg4 {or Nxe4 since Bxe1 is met by the intermediate} Nd6 {.}) 12. Nxe4 dxe4 13. Nc3 {Here is the point: the knight has the c3 -square, attacking the e4 -pawn.} Bb4 {The only move to stop White from capturing the e4 -pawn.} 14. Re3 {White takes the rook out of the pin, and now Nxe4 is a threat again.} Bxc3 15. bxc3 {Even though it is an opposite-colored bishops position, White is attacking. After Rg3 , Black is going to face a lot of issues; Ba3 - d6 is another idea as well.} *

