 .} 19. Rac1 {(the silly engine suggests Qf5 to only move the queen again next move, so we'll ignore that) − White is a pawn down but with a completely winning position, whereas Black has to consider hopeless moves like ... Kd7 and wait for the inevitable 1-0.}) 11. d5 {If we closely examine the position, we will see that Black cannot develop the kingside. After d5 , the position is paralyzed, while Qb3 and Bg5 are very powerful too.} *

