he main line.}) 14. Bg5 {Black is forced to find an only move, which is not easy for any chess player.} (14. Nxd5 {doesn't work in view of} b5 15. Qb3 Nxe5 16. Rxe5 Bd6 17. Bg5 {( Re1 Bxh2+ followed by ... Qh4 is hopeless for White.)} Qb8 {and Black is on the good side of the complications.}) (14. Nxg6 hxg6 {and now} 15. Nxd5 {can be met similarly with} b5 {(more human than the mysterious Rh5} 16. Nf4 {Rb5 , which is the engine's suggestion) Qb3} Bd6 17. g3 O-O {, when White struggles given the weaker structure.}) 14... Be7 ({This natural move is losing immediately.} 14... Qc8 {is also losing because after} 15. Rac1 {, either Nb5 or Nd5 is impossible to stop.}) (14... f6 {doesn't work either since after} 15. Nxg6 hxg6 16. Rxe6+ Kf7 17. Qb3 {, all the tactics see White on top.}) 15. Bxe7 Qxe7 16. Nxd5 {And here we understand the reason why we pushed the bishop on e4 away. Black cannot capture on d5 since the rook on e1 would join the game and Black would lose the queen.} Qd6 17. Qxd7+ Qxd7 18. Nxd7 Kxd7 19. Nb6+ {White will be an exchange up, with a winning endgame.} *

