he main line.}) 14. Bg5 {Black is forced to find an only move, which is not easy for any chess player.} (14. Nxd5 {doesn't work in view of} b5 15. Qb3 Nxe5 16. Rxe5 Bd6 17. Bg5 {( Re1 Bxh2+ followed by ... Qh4 is hopeless for White.)} Qb8 {and Black is on the good side of the complications.}) (14. Nxg6 hxg6 {and now} 15. Nxd5 {can be met similarly with} b5 {(more human than the mysterious Rh5} 16. Nf4 {Rb5 , which is the engine's suggestion) Qb3} Bd6 17. g3 O-O {, when White struggles given the weaker structure.}) 14... b5 ({This strong intermezzo is the only way for Black to keep the game going and not lose immediately.} 14... Qc8 {is losing because after} 15. Rac1 {, either Nb5 or Nd5 is impossible to stop.}) (14... f6 {doesn't work either since after} 15. Nxg6 hxg6 16. Rxe6+ Kf7 17. Qb3 {, all the tactics see White on top.}) 15. Nxb5 axb5 16. Qxb5 Qc7 {This move is natural. The idea is to keep the material advantage, but it is not smart, in this case, as White is winning the game with a beautiful tactic.} 17. Rac1 Qa7 18. Qc6 {A powerful move, with multiple ideas: one is Qc8 +, another idea is to take on d7 and Black's rook on a8 would not be protected anymore, and also Nxg6 followed by Rxe6 is another mating idea. As you can guess, it is impossible to stop all these ideas at the same time.} *

