O {is no longer a valid option since after} 14. b4 {followed by Rb1 and b5 , Black will suffer in the long run. Better is} e5 {to get more space in the center and castle queenside next, but that would hand us nice play on the light squares following} 15. Nh4 {and Qf3 , while b4 can be thrown in as well. The position is murky, when all three results are on the table.}) 13. Nh4 {White's idea is to bring the queen to h5 .} O-O 14. Qh5 {White's attack is extremely powerful, and practically it is impossible to stop. Re3 with the Nf5 follow-up is the idea.} *

