 of the game.} Qc7 13. Qe3 b6 ({Black has to try to develop the bishop as soon as possible.} 13... b5 {is another way, when we'll ignore the pawn on b5 for obvious reasons. We'll continue to develop with} 14. Bd3 {followed by castling kingside since castling queenside is no longer desirable given the counterplay ... b4 would yield.}) 14. Bd3 Bb7 15. O-O-O Rac8 16. Rhe1 {White has developed all the pieces and can already focus on the attack with Ng5 or Qe4 .} *

