1. e4 c5 ({To White's 1.e4 , the Sicilian Defense is the most popular response. The opening has a reputation for leading to very sharp positions, yet it also depends on how both sides decide to keep the game going. After} 1... c5 {, we are going to play mostly sidelines where Black has to play very carefully.}) 2. Nf3 ({This is the most logical and sound move here, simply developing the knight. Usually, the idea is to push} 2. d4 {, but in some cases, we are going to make different moves, avoiding main line theory.}) 2... e6 {This is probably one of the oldest approaches in chess history, and it leads to many theoretical discussions such as the Paulsen or Taimanov.} 3. d4 cxd4 4. Qxd4 {This is an extremely rare idea, and a very strange-looking one as well. The point is to keep the knight on f3 and place the queen on e3 after ... Nc6 .} Nc6 5. Qe3 Nf6 6. Nc3 {This is the main position of this line. Here Black has many options, and we are going to react to each of these options in different ways.} d6 {A solid move, stopping the e4 - e5 idea.} 7. b3 {This is an amazing idea − the bishop on b2 is very strong, as castling long is quite safe in general.} Be7 8. Bb2 O-O 9. O-O-O a6 ({This position can also occur after} 9... a6 {.}) 10. h3 {The threat is to push e4 - e5 while h3 protects the g4 -square, so ... Ng4 would not be an option, and it also prepares a scary attack.} Qc7 (10... Qa5 {will only be in the way of Black's counterplay on the queenside, so we can respond in similar fashion with} 11. g4 {.}) 11. g4 b5 {Black has to try to create a counterattack.} 12. g5 Nd7 13. Nh2 {This is an amazing move, with a very deep idea. After the f2 - f4 push, the knight goes to g4 , the rook to g1 , and Black has to watch out for ideas like Nh6 or Nf6 .} Bb7 {This move is very natural and does seem very strong as well, with the idea of ... Rac8 .} 14. f4 Rac8 15. Ng4 Nb4 {This looks like a very strong move, creating the ... Nxa2 + threat and ... Nxc2 followed up by ... b4 .} 16. Rh2 {A very classy move, defending the c2 -pawn, and Black's attack is gone. The next move is a3 , and after the danger is gone, we can continue our attack with f5 - f6 .} *

