1. e4 c5 ({To White's 1.e4 , the Sicilian Defense is the most popular response. The opening has a reputation for leading to very sharp positions, yet it also depends on how both sides decide to keep the game going. After} 1... c5 {, we are going to play mostly sidelines where Black has to play very carefully.}) 2. Nf3 ({This is the most logical and sound move here, simply developing the knight. Usually, the idea is to push} 2. d4 {, but in some cases, we are going to make different moves, avoiding main line theory.}) 2... Nc6 {This move has always been very popular; the main idea of this opening is to play the Sveshnikov Defense, but with our third move, we avoid those lines.} 3. Bb5 g6 {This move became extremely popular during the World Championship match between Caruana and Carlsen, and after that, a lot of people started to study the Rossolimo.} 4. c3 {Usually, Black's idea is to go ... Bg7 and ... e5 , and for now, with c3 , we are trying to take the center with d4 .} Nf6 {This is the only move to stop the d4 push and White's control in the center.} ({Following} 4... Bg7 5. d4 cxd4 6. cxd4 Nf6 7. Nc3 {, White is already better, and Black has to watch out for e5 as well.}) 5. e5 Nd5 6. O-O Bg7 {A logical move, trying to finish development.} 7. d4 cxd4 (7... O-O {does not make a lot of sense. It is just a free pawn for White after} 8. dxc5 {, and Black does not have compensation.}) 8. cxd4 O-O 9. Nc3 {The knight on d5 is extremely strong and that is the reason why we are fine with the trade of knights.} Nc7 10. Bf4 {Although giving up the bishop pair may make this move look odd, the goal is to prevent Black from developing peacefully.} Nxb5 11. Nxb5 {Now ... d6 is not an option.} a6 12. Nc3 d6 (12... d5 {would get the same treatment.}) 13. exd6 exd6 {Thus far, all of the moves seem quite simple, and the games are displaying the same.} 14. d5 {This is the point of having the bishop on f4 : now the e5 -square is guarded.} Ne7 (14... Ne5 15. Nxe5 dxe5 16. Be3 {grants us a strong passed pawn on d5 .}) 15. Qd2 {The knight on e7 has no future, White controls more space, and Black, despite having two bishops, is in a difficult position. We can easily take control of the e-file, and stopping Ne4 is difficult.} *

