1. e4 c6 {The Caro-Kann is one of the most solid openings in the history of chess. Players who prefer a more solid and defensive style often choose the Caro-Kann, as it helps to avoid some of the sharp and tactical lines of other openings. The main idea is that no matter what White plays, Black's next move is an obvious one, and that is going to be ... d7 - d5 , challenging White's central pawn.} 2. d4 d5 3. e5 {By taking space right from the beginning, we can play the game in the best and most principled way.} c5 ({There are two main moves after e5 , and} 3... c5 {is one of them. The objective is to challenge White's center as soon as possible.}) 4. Nf3 ({This is the second most common move in this position. The most played move is} 4. dxc5 {, which leads to a huge amount of theory. With Nf3 , we are able to keep an advantage and I believe it is much easier to play and to remember the ideas.}) 4... Nc6 5. dxc5 ({Here as well, the main move is Bg4 , but after} 5. Bb5 {, it transposes to the 4...Bg4 line .}) 5... e6 6. Be3 {Protecting the pawn and developing the pieces is always a good idea.} Nge7 (6... Nh6 {is the same as Nge7 , while Bxc5? may seem like a very smart tactical resource, but it does not work. Bxc5 Qa5+} 7. b4 $1 {and White stays a piece up.}) 7. c3 {This is always a strong and prophylactic move. I believe it is the best approach when it comes to online chess and fast games.} ({Here, we do not have to remember two different lines, against Nge7 and Nh6 . We are going to play the same thing:} 7. c3 {, which stops ... Qa5 checks in the future and also enables b2 - b4 ideas as well.}) 7... Nf5 8. Qd2 {As long as we maintain the pawn advantage, Black has a very difficult time equalizing.} (8. Bd4 {doesn't guarantee a superior position due to the clever} Bd7 {(prophylaxis against Bb5 ), and Black threatens to throw in a disruptive ... b6 with a strong initiative. Now} 9. Bb5 {is well met by the tactical trick} Nxe5 10. Nxe5 Bxb5 {, when White has lost all the advantage.}) 8... Qc7 9. Bd4 {The bishop on d4 looks a little bit odd, but it does the job of defending our pawns, and right now the main idea is to finish development with Bd3 , O-O , and later on we can try to push b4 and make the c5 -pawn stronger; Bd3xf5 is also a good option to eliminate the strong knight on f5 .} *

