{This is by far the most common in this position. The main idea is to bring the e7 -knight to c6 and try to put pressure on the d4 -pawn.} 9. Nd2 Nc6 10. Qg3 {A powerful move! It is important not to go Nf3 very early in this case. The idea of Qg3 is very simple: we are stopping Black from castling short, when it is hard for Black to develop with the logical ... Be7 since the g7 -pawn is hanging, while ... g7 - g6 would weaken the dark squares and after Nf3 , our c1 -bishop would become very powerful.} Qb6 {There are already no games in this position, but I believe that ... Qb6 is by far the most logical move, especially in a blitz game.} 11. Nf3 Qa6 (11... O-O-O {is a logical move that leads to a losing position:} 12. Ng5 {and Nf7 is unstoppable.}) 12. Re1 {As we can see, right now Black is having trouble with development; the king is in the middle of the board, and it is not possible to castle on either side.} cxd4 13. Nexd4 {Black is stuck in the middle of the board, and even if they were able to play ... O-O-O , the a4 and b4 pawn pushes would always be very annoying to play against, and they should always watch out for moves like Ng5 and Qf4 , attacking the weak f7 -pawn.} *

