their knight, which is on g8 at the moment.} Qb6 {Even though this is not the most common move in this exact position, I believe that this is the best way from Black's perspective.} 9. Nd2 Qa6 {This is a common queen trade idea, but in this case, the knight is on c6 , so the pawn structure would be ruined after the queen trade.} 10. Qxa6 bxa6 11. Nb3 {It is extremely important to force Black to touch the c5 -pawn, as otherwise, with ... a5 Black would be able to equalize.} cxd4 ({After} 11... c4 12. Nd2 Nge7 13. b3 {, we damage Black's pawn structure, and we also open up the rook's file, attacking the a6 -pawn.}) 12. cxd4 {Our next move will be Be3 , and then we will try to double our rooks on the c-file and use the fact that Black's pawns are doubled and cannot control the a5 and c5 -squares where we will try to penetrate with Nc3 - a4 .} *

