e d4 -pawn and prepare c3 .} Nxf4 14. Nxf4 Qc7 {A very natural move; for the moment, it is hard to protect the e5 -knight.} 15. Nh5 Nxh5 16. Qxh5 Be6 ({In case of} 16... Bxe5 17. dxe5 c5 18. c3 {, Black has to find} Qd8 {with the idea ... Qg5 , and after} 19. h4 c4 20. Bc2 d4 21. cxd4 Qxd4 22. Rad1 Qg4 {(The greedy Qxb2? is well met by} 23. Re2 {, when suddenly White gets a powerful initiative with f4 next. ) Qxg4 Bxg4 Rd4} Be6 24. f4 {, White has a tiny edge in the endgame.}) 17. Re3 {White has full control over the e-file. The plan is to bring the other rook to e1 and, depending on the situation, start the attack with either f4 - f5 or with the Rg3 and Qxh6 idea.} *

