1. e4 e6 {The French Defense is a popular chess opening characterized by Black's early pawn move to e6 , which creates a solid and defensive pawn structure. The French Defense is known for leading to positions with asymmetrical pawn structures and imbalanced pawn formations.} 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 (3. exd5 {is a very interesting move. It has somewhat of a reputation among amateur players that this is a way of making a draw, but that is not the case. I do like this move because it avoids all the complications, and I believe that with good preparation, White can put pressure on Black.}) 3... exd5 4. Nf3 {Black has a lot of options here, but people usually tend to copy our moves with ... Nf6 and ... Bd6 .} Bd6 5. c4 {By avoiding all the symmetrical positions, this move keeps the game dynamic and sharp.} c6 {This is one of the main moves, simply to protect the d-pawn.} 6. c5 {The objective of this move is to secure space on the queenside, setting the stage for any future maneuvers and for the coordination of our pieces. At some point, White will also try to make the b4 - b5 push work.} Bc7 7. Bd3 {There aren't many games that have been played in this unfamiliar position, but White has a simple idea to keep the game going.} Ne7 {Probably the best way to continue from Black's side, but our game plan does not change; we still want to take some control of the center and start pushing with b4 - b5 .} 8. O-O O-O 9. Re1 ({It's a novelty, and I like this move a lot. The main move is} 9. Nc3 {, and the most common response is} Bf5 {. With Re1 , we take the only open file, and we set a nice trap against ... Bf5 and ... Bg4 .}) 9... Bf5 {This is a very natural move, Black is trying to trade and get rid of our strong bishop.} (9... Bg4 $2 10. Bxh7+ {is a great tactical resource.} Kxh7 11. Ng5+ {, double attack, and with the next move, White is going to capture the g4 -bishop and stay a pawn up.}) 10. Rxe7 {Eliminating the defender.} Bxd3 11. Rxc7 Bxb1 12. Rxb7 {White stays a healthy pawn up, with a very active position. The only thing White needs to do now is to finish development with Bf4 and Qd2 .} *

