1. e4 d5 {This opening is referred to as the Scandinavian Defense or Scandinavian Opening. It is one of the oldest openings in the history of chess and also one of Magnus Carlsen's favorite openings in his blitz repertoire. Black initiates the game by opening up the position and forcing an open, dynamic battle.} 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qd8 ({It is less common to play the Scandinavian with} 3... Qd8 {. I think it's an interesting and solid option and the main idea of Qd8 is that, unlike Qa5 and Qd6 , Black's queen is not getting attacked by White's minor pieces.}) 4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 Bg4 {The most natural and the best move for Black.} 6. h3 Bxf3 7. Qxf3 c6 8. Be3 e6 9. Bd3 Nbd7 10. O-O {This is a great position for White, thanks to the bishop pair advantage, and the idea of bringing the knight to e4 and playing for c4 , as well as bringing the rooks to the center.} *

