1. e4 d5 {This opening is referred to as the Scandinavian Defense or Scandinavian Opening. It is one of the oldest openings in the history of chess and also one of Magnus Carlsen's favorite openings in his blitz repertoire. Black initiates the game by opening up the position and forcing an open, dynamic battle.} 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qd6 {The modern approach of the Scandinavian is probably the best try. Black's main idea is to keep the queen in the center of the board while keeping it active.} 4. d4 Nf6 5. Nge2 {This move isn't the most popular in this situation, but it has a very simple idea: White wants to attack the queen with Bf4 and get ahead in development.} g6 {The 5.Nge2 idea works extremely well, especially against the ... g6 systems, so playing ... g6 here is obviously logical, but it is extremely dangerous.} 6. Bf4 Qd8 7. Qd2 Bg7 8. O-O-O O-O 9. Bh6 {With the help of Ng3 , White is ready to launch the attack with h4 - h5 .} *

