{Black resigned here since Qd8 is met by Rb8+ .} 1. e4 {This game is a very good example of how dangerous the line is for Black.} c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. O-O a6 5. Bxd7+ Bxd7 6. c3 Nf6 7. Re1 Bc6 8. d4 Bxe4 9. Bg5 {Here we get the main position of this line, when there are many possible moves. Now ... Bxb1 is not the strongest, but it is also an option.} Bxb1 10. Rxb1 e6 11. Bxf6 Qxf6 12. dxc5 {A simple and very strong move.} O-O-O (12... dxc5 {is losing immediately:} 13. Ne5 Qe7 14. Qa4+ b5 15. Qe4 {and Black's king will not have time to castle. After Rbd1 next, White is completely winning.}) 13. c6 {A very strong move and it is almost over. Black's king simply does not have enough defenders around.} bxc6 14. Qa4 Kb7 15. Nd4 Rc8 16. b4 {Another very strong move by Riazantsev, opening up the rook's file in order to finish the game.} Rc7 17. b5 cxb5 18. Nxb5 axb5 19. Qxb5+ Kc8 20. Qe8+ *

